alwaysApply: true
---

Frontend conventions for SignalGraph:

- use clean, technical, investor-grade UI
- avoid hype-heavy visuals
- organize by pages, components, hooks/lib, and charts
- keep business logic out of presentational components
- use strongly typed data fetching contracts
- every score card should support:
  - numeric value
  - short interpretation
  - explanation details
  - raw contributing features where appropriate

Primary UX goals:
- make adjusted scores intuitive
- make score reasoning inspectable
- show uncertainty or missing-data states clearly
- allow comparison between raw popularity and trust-adjusted traction

Do not hide the difference between raw stars and adjusted scores.
Prefer clarity over visual novelty.
